gnized international forum for the exchange of ideas amongst linguists working on South Asia. The Annual Review of South Asian Languages and Linguistics is designed to be just that forum. It brings together empirical and theoretical research and serves as a testing ground for the articulation of new ideas and approaches which may be grounded in a study of South Asian languages but which have universal applicability. Each volume will have three major sections:I. Invited contributions consisting of state-of-the-art essays on research in South Asian languages.II. Refereed open submissions focusing on relevant issues and providing various viewpoints.III. Reports from around the world, book reviews and abstracts of doctoral theses.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aIndo-Aryan languages, Modern. 0aIndo-Aryan languages. 0aSociolinguisticszSouth Asia. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aAnsaldo, Umberto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBhattacharja, Shishir, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDasgupta, Probal, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPeterson, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRau, Felix, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSailaja, Pingali, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSharma, Ghanshyam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSharma, Ghanshyam, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSingh, Rajendra, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagez978311064977208iTitle is part of eBook 